ideas concerning legitimacy and the outward signs of authority. He does not ground legitimacy in legal abstractions, but rather on Philipp’s appearance. This kind of thinking is found not only in politics but also in feudal lay society and the literature derived from it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aKing Philip's War, 1675-1676. 4aHerrschaftszeichen. 4aPhilipp von Schwaben. 4aWalther von der Vogelweide. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aPhilipp of Swabia.  aSign of legitimacy.  aWalther von der Vogelweide.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket AV  Literaturwissenschaften 2013z9783110342703oZDB-23-ALW0 cprintz978311034454740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034461540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110344615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110344615/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-ALWb2013  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014